How to Create Mysql Server with Replication:

1) Install mysql on two servers or create two containers of mysql of same version.
2) One is master and other is slave (Replica).
3) Login to master mysql-server.
4) vim /etc/mysql/conf.d/master.cnf
5)  [mysqld]
	server-id=1
	log_bin=mysql-bin
	binlog_do_db=mydb   # optional: replicate only this DB if you want all comment this line
5) save and quit.
6) Login to slave mysql-server.
7) vim /etc/mysql/conf.d/slave.conf
8) [mysqld]
	server-id=2
	relay-log=relay-log
9) save and quit
10) Restart both container or mysql-server

11) login to slave system and use the following configuration
CREATE USER 'replica'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'Pass@1234';
GRANT REPLICATION SLAVE ON *.* TO 'replica'@'%';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
SHOW MASTER STATUS;

12) Now login to  slave system and add the folowing configuration.
CHANGE MASTER TO
  MASTER_HOST='master',
  MASTER_USER='replica',
  MASTER_PASSWORD='Pass@1234',
  MASTER_LOG_FILE='mysql-bin.000001',
  MASTER_LOG_POS=154;

START SLAVE;

13) show slave status\G
Slave_IO_Running: Yes
Slave_SQL_Running: Yes
Seconds_Behind_Master: 0

14) if you getting same that means config done.

